    multi_group_vignette normtest workflow

    Function reference

    All functions

    cf()
    Set rownames to a specified column and remove that column from the dataframe
    check_means()
    check if two or more group means are zero
    combine_fc_pvals()
    combine fold changes and pvals into single dataframe. takes column i from data1 and column i from data2 and puts them next to each other
    fold_change()
    The fold_change function iterates through the groups specified by var1 to calculate the log2FoldChange of mean(groupA) / mean(groupB). Note that this function will order the groups alphabetically before proceding, and a column named "log2FoldChange_GroupB_vs_GroupA" is reporting log2(mean(GroupA) / mean(groupB))
    p.adjustment.methods
    Dunns multicomparison test from dunn.test library
    rui()
    This function puts together all the multigroup functions from the package in the correct order.
    run_anova()
    Runs a two way anova based on var1 * var2 for each row of my_data
    run_dunn()
    Runs Dunn's multi comparison test on each row of my_data
    run_dunnett()
    Runs DunnettT3 multi comparison test on each row of my_data
    run_kruskal()
    Run Kruskal-Wallis test on each row of my_data
    run_ttest()
    Runs an unpaired t-test on each row of my_data and reports the p value, computed by t.test
    run_tukey()
    Runs a Tukey multicomparison test on each row of my_data based on var1
    run_welch()
    Runs a Welch t-test on each row of my_data
    run_wilcox()
    Runs two sided Wilcoxon Rank Sum test on each row of my_data and reports the p value, computed by wilcox.test
    test_norm()
    For at least 3 groups. Test and sort data by distribution and variance equality
    two_group_rui()
    This function puts together all the two group functions from the package in the correct order.
    two_group_test_norm()
    For exactly two groups. Test and sort data by distribution and equality of variances
